<div id='communityQuestionsWithAnswers'>
<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
<a class="spoiler" href="/questions/1509229-i-m-about-20-in-and-i-had-to-stop-reading">This question contains spoilers...</a>
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[I'm about 20% in and I had to stop reading it because it was so upsetting. Does the emotional heaviness change after the murder? I really want to continue on but am not sure it's worth sending me into a bit of a depression. I seem to have this issue with books at times. I wonder if I should just give up or push through. <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1509229'><a id="like_count_community_question_1509229" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1509229?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F15622.Native_Son">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1509229-i-m-about-20-in-and-i-had-to-stop-reading">2 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1509229-i-m-about-20-in-and-i-had-to-stop-reading">See all 2 answers</a>
</li>
